{
  "text": "It has been recently demonstrated that a fusion between vg and the TEA domain of sd encodes a protein that functions like the native VG/SD transcription complex in the context of wing formation. This fusion can rescue sd or vg single mutations as well as the double mutant wing phenotype [CITATION_1] . Several lines of evidence suggest that this rescue could be happening via the wg pathway. Firstly, clonal analysis of sd mutations has shown that wing discs are deficient in specific aspects of wg expression [CITATION_2] . Secondly, it has been proposed that sd can induce wg expression [CITATION_3] and might be involved in the maintenance of the wg D/V specific expression [CITATION_4] . Thirdly, the role of wg in growth and proliferation of the cells in the wing disc is well documented (Diaz-Benjumea and [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . Finally, transdetermination of leg disc cells to wing-like cells is achieved by overexpression of wg in the leg disc [CITATION_9] . Thus, it is likely that the rescue of the sd wing phenotype by the fusion construct [CITATION_10] is mediated by wg.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "45466002",
